**Steps to Reproduce**:

```c#
using System;
public class C {
    private class Trace {
        public void Write(String value) {
        }
    }
    Trace _trace = new Trace();
    
    public void M() {
        _trace.Write("2");
        try 
        {
            _trace.Write("3");
            try 
            {
                _trace.Write("4");
            } 
            finally 
            {
                _trace.Write("5");
                try 
                {
                    _trace.Write("6");
                    throw new System.ArgumentException();
                } 
                finally 
                {
                    _trace.Write("7");
                }
            }
        } 
        finally 
        {
            _trace.Write("8");
        }
    }
}
```
The IL that is generated contains a loop at the end of outer most `try block`.  Check out [sharplab output](https://sharplab.io/#v2:).

![IL Output](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12488060/107837758-5b85a680-6d57-11eb-90e8-73eb975e5ef0.png)


**Expected Behavior**:
No loop present at the end of outermost try block.

**Actual Behavior**:
Loop present at the end of outermost try block.

